id: pm-vhbf
title: "pm schema list-fields / show-field / add-field / remove-field: CLI management of schema/fields.json"
description: "Runtime custom fields (schema/fields.json) are the schema customization mechanism that lets projects add typed metadata columns with CLI flags, but the schema command family has no subcommands for them. Unlike types and statuses (which have add-type/remove-type/add-status/remove-status), custom fields require hand-editing schema/fields.json. pm schema list also doesn't display registered custom fields. This is a significant UX gap in the 'universal customization' story."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:cli","area:schema",customization,dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:08:11.019Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-17T05:54:35.975Z"
author: audit-cli-schema-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- pm schema list includes a 'fields' section showing registered custom fields (key, type, commands, cli_flag)\n- pm schema show-field <key> shows full field definition\n- pm schema add-field <key> --type <type> --commands create,update --description <text> [--required] [--required-on-create] [--allow-unset] [--cli-flag <flag>] [--alias <alias>] manages schema/fields.json\n- pm schema remove-field <key> removes entry from schema/fields.json with advisory usage count\n- pm schema add-field is idempotent (upsert); warns if key shadows a builtin field name\n- CONFIGURATION.md documents schema/fields.json format and example field definitions\n- Shell completions and flag contracts updated"
goal: Let any project define project-specific metadata fields via CLI without editing JSON files by hand
value: Completes the schema/config universal-customization story by closing the last CLI-inaccessible schema primitive
parent: pm-8jdc
risk: medium
confidence: high
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-17T05:13:30.431Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented schema list-fields/show-field/add-field/remove-field + a fields section in schema list. New core module src/core/schema/fields-file.ts (parse/serialize/upsertField/removeField/normalizeAddFieldInput + BUILTIN_FIELD_KEYS guard + normalizeFieldKey), modeled on item-types-file.ts/status-defs-file.ts; added SCHEMA_FIELDS_LOCK_ID. Run fns runSchemaAddField/RemoveField/ListFields/ShowField in schema.ts (existing IO c8-ignore block) reuse resolveRuntimeFieldRegistry; remove-field emits advisory items_using_field counts via new countItemsUsingField(listAllFrontMatterLight). add-field idempotent UPSERT keyed on normalized key, rejects built-in-shadowing keys, allow_unset defaults true. Surfaces wired: commander flags type/commands/cli-flag/required/required-on-create/no-allow-unset/required-types/alias, SCHEMA_FLAG_CONTRACTS, MCP pm_schema enum+props, tool-parameter-tables, PM_TOOL_ACTION_SCHEMA_CONTRACTS optional+conditionalRequired, server.ts dispatch args+options, completion bash/zsh/fish, COMMANDS.md +CONFIGURATION.md cross-ref. list shape CHANGED: added top-level fields:{custom,counts}. Coverage 100/100/100/100. Tests: fields-file.spec.ts, schema-command field describe, register-commands routing, mcp-handshake CRUD. Lead closes."
  "2026-06-17T05:54:35.975Z",claude-code-agent,"CodeRabbit PR#259 hardening: upsertField/removeField collapse/remove ALL normalized-key matches (hand-authored fields.json may carry duplicate entries) not just first; MCP pm_schema 'name' param description extended to cover custom field keys. +duplicate-key tests, 100% cov."
close_reason: "Added: pm schema add-field/remove-field/list-fields/show-field manage schema/fields.json (new core/schema/fields-file.ts mirroring item-types-file/status-defs-file with SCHEMA_FIELDS_LOCK_ID); pm schema list now includes a fields section. Custom runtime fields are now fully CLI-managed instead of hand-edited."
body: "## Context\n\nThe runtime field system is fully implemented:\n- schema/fields.json is loaded and merged by loadRuntimeSchemaFromOptionalFiles (src/core/schema/runtime-schema.ts:514-602)\n- RuntimeFieldDefinition is validated and resolved by normalizeRuntimeFieldDefinition (runtime-schema.ts:238-278)\n- Runtime field flags are dynamically registered on create/update/list/search/context commands (src/cli/main.ts:785-808)\n- Fields can specify type (string/number/boolean/string_array), commands, required_on_create, allow_unset, cli_flag, cli_aliases\n\nBut:\n- pm schema list (SchemaListResult) does NOT include a 'fields' section (src/cli/commands/schema.ts:163-187)\n- SCHEMA_SUBCOMMANDS (schema.ts:42-51) = ['add-type','remove-type','add-status','remove-status','list','show','show-status'] — no field subcommands\n- No field-specific lock like SCHEMA_TYPES_LOCK_ID/SCHEMA_STATUSES_LOCK_ID exists for fields\n- CONFIGURATION.md has zero mention of schema/fields.json or RuntimeFieldDefinition\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- pm schema list includes a 'fields' section showing registered custom fields (key, type, commands, cli_flag)\n- pm schema show-field <key> shows full field definition\n- pm schema add-field <key> --type <type> --commands create,update --description <text> [--required] [--required-on-create] [--allow-unset] [--cli-flag <flag>] [--alias <alias>] manages schema/fields.json\n- pm schema remove-field <key> removes entry from schema/fields.json with advisory usage count\n- pm schema add-field is idempotent (upsert); warns if key shadows a builtin field name\n- CONFIGURATION.md documents schema/fields.json format and example field definitions\n- Shell completions and flag contracts updated\n\n## Evidence\n\n- src/core/schema/runtime-schema.ts:238-278 (normalizeRuntimeFieldDefinition — shows all field properties)\n- src/core/schema/runtime-schema.ts:514-602 (loadRuntimeSchemaFromOptionalFiles — reads fields.json)\n- src/cli/commands/schema.ts:42-51 (SCHEMA_SUBCOMMANDS — no field subcommands)\n- src/cli/commands/schema.ts:163-187 (SchemaListResult — no fields array)\n- src/core/schema/item-types-file.ts and status-defs-file.ts (implementation pattern to follow for fields-file.ts)"
